@node intro "Introduction"

This door was written for multi-node BBS's like Redrum BBS as a replacement
for the WHO online function in MAX's :)

The advantages are :-

Screen updates itself every second giving a precise status of all nodes.

Shows User name, Users location & Current action! (Scanning mail etc etc)

Also shows which nodes are accepting fidonet mail polls!

@endnode
@node sysreq "System Requirements"

This door **REQUIRES**  MAX's BBS Professional v1.00+!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

It's also useful to have a multi-node BBS :)

@endnode
@node inst "Installation & Configs"

The easy bit :^)... Just use the following:-

	Lha X NSA_Who.Lha Doors:
	
This will work for any system that has Doors: assigned to where the BBS has
it's doors..

You will need the NSAkeyfile.key in S: for this program to work.

This is FREE!!!!!!!!..  Run the door for more info :)


Running
~~~~~~~

Execution under MAX's Pro v1 - v1.70
In the menu editor set.

Key:   Function:  Extra:    Lo Acc:    Hi Acc:	  Filename/Name/Dest/Path:
 /       34	    0 	     10000	10000	  Doors:WHO/Who_Online +

Remember the +!!!!  It starts it as a MAX's Pro door :))))

It's a good idea to change the ANSI file supplied with this door!!!!

Otherwise peeps will think they've called Redrum :)

@endnode

@node inuse "Using NSA Who Online when started :))))))"

Just sit there and watch the display basically :)

If a user is running a door then you'll see the door name in brackets :))

The display looks like...

------------------------------------------------------------------------

01     Niki Murkett        Redrum SysOp Team     Scanning Mail

02     Niki Murkett        Redrum SysOp Team     Door (Who_Online)

03     Awaiting Connect

------------------------------------------------------------------------

The way the system works to hack the info out sometimes cocks up :(

This is unavoidable, so please don't send any bug reports about it :)


I think that's about it now :)))))))))))))

(Read the credz & greetz :))) )


@endnode

